### Issue: `_configure_db` called on every new connection — redundant but not wrong

**Location**: `record_event()` (line 233), `_init_db()` (line 117), `_migrate_legacy_jsonl_if_needed()` (line 156), `_load_records_after()` (line 427)

Every `sqlite3.connect` gets its own connection-local PRAGMA settings. Calling `_configure_db` each time is correct (new connection = new defaults). Not a bug, just worth noting if someone later switches to a persistent connection — they'd only need to set it once.

